<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With three of this week's new programs set in London, Kenya and New York, 
viewers are treated to a world of choices on both network and local TV. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Caine (upper left) stars in "Jekyll &amp; Hyde," a new TV movie remake 
of the Robert Louis Stevenson tale about a tormented English doctor confronted 
with his evil alter ego. 
</P>
<P>
Cheryl Ladd co-stars in the two-hour film airing Sunday at 9 p.m. on Channels 
7, 3, 10 and 42. 
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday at 9 p.m. (Channels 2 and 8), CBS offers "Face to Face," a 
"Hallmark Hall of Fame" production starring Elizabeth Montgomery and Robert 
Foxworth as a paleontologist and miner, respectively, who clash when both claim 
digging rights to the same territory in Africa. 
</P>
<P>
Originating in New York, "House Party" is a weekday series hosted by Steve 
Doocy, formerly of WRC-TV in Washington. The hourlong mix of information and 
entertainment premieres Monday at 10 a.m. on KNBC-TV Channel 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
