<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARK'S TRAFFIC IDEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Eisner, Disney's chairman, is expecting federal government assistance 
to build roads and solve traffic problems in Anaheim or Long Beach before he 
can consent to building a new Disneyland Park. 
</P>
<P>
This is a charming idea. Since we in Orange County are unable to find federal 
money to solve our existing freeway problems, Eisner, if successful in 
obtaining federal money, might consider sharing Disneyland profits -- so we can 
solve our traffic problems. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID G. BAKER 
</P>
<P>
Yorba Linda 
</P>
