<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUGH SMITH ELECTED TO LEAD APARTMENT ASSN. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hugh Smith, a Pasadena residential and commercial property owner, has been 
elected 1990 president of the California Apartment Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Other new officers of the Sacramento-based trade group are John Alioto, San 
Diego, president-elect; Dwight Long, Fresno, vice president; Robert A. Diaz, 
Norco, treasurer; Ted Kimball, San Diego, secretary, and Larry Hull, Santa 
Clara, immediate past president. 
</P>
