<HEADLINE>
<P>
COBA CLARIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reason I am writing to you is to point out a couple of inaccuracies in 
Steve Weinstein's piece, "Uncovering Coba" (Jan. 7). 
</P>
<P>
The article refers to "a pair of lakes." There are actually four lakes in the 
immediate vicinity of the ruins. Another statement: "The pyramid of Nohoch Mul 
towers more than 100 feet above the jungle floor. . . ." The statement is 
correct, but the actual height is about 140 feet. 
</P>
<P>
H. DEON HOLT 
</P>
<P>
Oceanside 
</P>
