<TEXT>
<P>
I have eradicated the Medflies from my navel orange tree in my back yard simply 
by using a fly swatter. A Medfly first appeared on my orange tree about three 
months ago. 
</P>
<P>
I called the Department of Agriculture about them. They said they had traps in 
my area. 
</P>
<P>
I then discovered that the Medfly is not as quick as a housefly. You could 
practically place your hand over the orange before they would fly away. 
</P>
<P>
