<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AIDS HOSPICE: A groundbreaking ceremony will be held Wednesday at the site of 
the nation's first hospice designed specifically to serve black and Latino AIDS 
victims. The ceremony will take place from 1 to 3 p.m. at 2146 W. Adams Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
SENATE FORUM: Candidates vying to replace Republican state Sen. William 
Campbell, whose 31st District includes portions of Los Angeles and Orange 
counties, will speak at a forum Wednesday evening at the La Habra City Council 
chambers. 
</P>
<P>
SNOW DAY: Never mind what the weather report says. It will snow in Cerritos on 
Wednesday. For the eighth consecutive year, 10 tons of ice will be shredded 
into snow and dumped on the parking lot at Gahr High School for about 300 
youngsters and their parents. The annual Snow Day is sponsored by the ABC 
Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
ETHNIC COMPLAINTS: Emerging ethnic groups representing the Cambodian, Armenian, 
Arab, Guatemalan, Iranian, Russian-Jewish, Samoan, Tongan, Salvadoran and 
Ethiopian communities are scheduled to testify Thursday at the Glendale City 
Council chambers in a public hearing called by the Los Angeles County 
Commission on Human Relations. Representatives of these groups have complained 
that government services are not meeting their custom and language needs. 
</P>
