<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGHT HALTS PALMDALE-ANTELOPE VALLEY MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Golden League soccer match between Palmdale High and host Antelope Valley was 
suspended Friday night with 10 minutes remaining when a fight erupted between 
Palmdale's Robert Rossil and Antelope Valley's Pablo Hernandez, according to 
Palmdale Coach Juan Paolo. 
</P>
<P>
Paolo and game and school officials will view videotapes of the match today to 
determine who was at fault in the altercation, the second this school year 
involving a Palmdale team. 
</P>
<P>
On Oct. 13, a football game between Palmdale and Saugus was stopped midway 
through the fourth quarter when Palmdale safety Darius Wilson attacked a game 
official. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley led, 2-1, Friday before referee Carlos Cerda ordered the match 
stopped. 
</P>
<P>
Cerda declared the match "no contest," Paolo said, and the records of Antelope 
Valley (4-1-1, 2-1-1 in league play) and Palmdale (2-4-7, 1-1-2) remained 
unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
