<P>
POSSIBLE CONFLICT IN NUCLEAR PLANT AUDITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least two firms hired by the Energy Department as independent investigators 
of environmental and safety conditions at nuclear weapons plants are on the 
payroll at facilities they investigated, government records show. 
</P>
<P>
Others participating in the audits had bid for Energy Department contracts at 
sites they studied, although they were not yet working there. Still others, 
while not associated with the plants they audited, are prime contractors at 
other nuclear bomb factories. Department guidelines for carrying out the 
"independent tiger team" investigations include a provision aimed at avoiding 
organizational conflicts of interest. 
</P>
