entanglement in the Lincoln S&amp;L debacle. It came during a community forum 
on drugs in Norwalk where Cranston, above, seemed elated -- scribbling notes 
and applauding at times. For Cranston-watchers, this was the signal that he 
will remain determined to run for a fifth term in 1992. LORI SHEPLER / Los 
Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
