SUSPECT ARRESTED IN SLASHING OF ACTRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 18-year-old man was arrested Saturday and charged with slashing actress 
Viveca Lindfors and a second person with a razor last weekend. He had been 
drinking and had taken LSD, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, Peter Bedford, was arrested at a friend's house in Brooklyn after 
police received an anonymous tip, said Manhattan Chief of Detectives Ronald 
Fenrich. 
</P>
<P>
Bedford was charged with two counts of assault and one count of criminal 
possession of a deadly weapon, Fenrich said. The razor allegedly used in the 
attacks was not recovered. 
</P>
<P>
Bedford is accused of slashing Lindfors, 69, and Dennis Beal, 36, on the face 
and head in separate incidents in Greenwich Village. The attacks occurred about 
3 blocks and five minutes apart. 
</P>
<P>
Both victims said they were accosted by a gang of young people and one member 
of the gang did the slashing. 
</P>
<P>
The Swedish-born Lindfors, who appeared in the movie "The Way We Were," needed 
27 stitches after the attack. Beal required 40 stitches to close his wound. 
</P>
