<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOS letter -- A Jan. 14 letter to the editor from Sylvia Easton, chairwoman of 
the Irvine Task Force for the Homeless, regarding the closing of Share Our 
Selves, was incorrectly edited to indicate that about 200,000 needy die in 
Orange County each year. The meaning intended was that if the 200,000 who seek 
services from SOS each year were turned away, many could die. 
</P>
