<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELUS LEAGUE BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI COMES BACK FOR 68-53 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG GONZALEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TORRANCE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After every basket Mater Dei High School scores, the Monarch fans yell, 
"Whoosh!" 
</P>
<P>
That was something like the sound Mater Dei made as it raced past Bishop 
Montgomery in the second half to beat the Knights, 68-53, in an Angelus League 
game at Bishop Montgomery Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
It was no easy victory for the Monarchs (20-1 overall, 4-0 in the Angelus 
League), the Southern Section's top-rated 5-A team. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery fell to 11-4 overall, 3-1 in the league. 
</P>
<P>
"(Bishop Montgomery) is a good team, they are a true contender," Mater Dei 
Coach Gary McKnight said. "(Bishop Montgomery Coach) Doug Mitchell has done a 
great job with them. The Angelus League is stronger than people think; it'll 
show up in the playoffs." 
</P>
<P>
The Knights were winless in the league last season. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei trailed, 31-28, at halftime, but led the third quarter with a 19-0 
run that spanned the period's first four minutes and 29 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell called two timeouts during the spurt and yelled to his team that "the 
game wasn't over." 
</P>
<P>
But after Dan O'Neil hit a 15-footer to the right of the basket with 3:23 left 
in the third quarter for a 47-31 lead, the game was virtually out of reach. 
</P>
<P>
"The kids got together at halftime and just decided that they were going to 
play together," McKnight said. 
</P>
<P>
Said Mitchell: "We played hard, but we didn't play intelligent. When they 
started that run, we panicked, we started (putting) up bad shots. Hopefully, it 
was a learning experience." 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei is a good team to learn from as the Monarchs committed only three 
second-half turnovers in wearing down Bishop Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
In the first half, Bishop Montgomery struggled to build a 26-18 lead with 4:22 
left in the second quarter. Mater Dei began forcing the Knights into 
cross-court passes, three of which were intercepted and led to baskets. The 
Monarchs cut the lead to three points, and the first half ended with Bishop 
Montgomery leading, 31-28. 
</P>
<P>
Darrell Daniel scored 15 points in the first two quarters, but then was held to 
one three-point basket in the second half. He led Bishop Montgomery with 18 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei guard David Boyle led all scorers with 21 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
